the year-long hiatus taken by the AFL.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.arenafan.com/news/?page=pressrel&article=11617|title=ESPN Acquires Rights to Arena Football Starting in 2014|date=December 17, 2013|work=Arena Football League|publisher=Arenafan.com|accessdate=August 19, 2014|location=Chicago, Illinois}}</ref>\n\n==2000s==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|'''ArenaBowl number'''\n|'''Year'''\n|'''Network'''\n|'''Play-by-play man'''\n|'''Color commentator(s)'''\n|'''Sideline reporter(s)'''\n|-\n|[[ArenaBowl XXII]]\n|[[2008 Arena Football League season|2008]]\n|[[Arena Football League on ESPN|ABC]]\n|[[Bob Wischusen]]\n|[[Ray Bentley]]\n|[[Stan Verrett]] and [[Marcellus Wiley]]\n|-\n|[[ArenaBowl XXI]]\n|[[2007 Arena Football League season|2007]]\n|[[Arena Football League on ESPN|ABC]]\n|[[Mike Greenberg]]\n|[[Mike Golic]]\n|\n|-\n|[[ArenaBowl XX]]<ref>{{YouTube|title=Arena Bowl XX|id=X2TLQG9vUck}}</ref>  \n|[[2006 Arena Football League season|2006]]\n|[[AFL on NBC|NBC]]\n|[[Tom Hammond]]\n|[[Pat Haden]]\n|[[Lewis Johnson]] and [[Marty Snider]]\n|-\n|[[ArenaBowl XIX]] \n|[[2005 Arena Football League season|2005]]\n|[[The AFL on NBC|NBC]] \n|[[Tom Hammond]]\n|[[Pat Haden]]\n|[[Lewis Johnson]] and [[Marty Snider]]\n|-\n|[[ArenaBowl XVIII]] \n|[[2004 Arena Football League season|2004]]\n|[[AFL on NBC|NBC]] \n|[[Tom Hammond]]\n|[[Pat Haden]]\n|[[Lewis Johnson]] and [[Marty Snider]]\n|-\n|[[ArenaBowl XVII]] \n|[[2003 Arena Football League season|2003]]\n|[[AFL on NBC|NBC]] \n|[[Tom Hammond]]\n|[[Pat Haden]]\n|[[Lewis Johnson]] and [[Marty Snider]]\n|-\n|[[ArenaBowl XVI]]<ref>{{YouTube|title=2002 Arena Bowl (Arena Football Championship: San Jose Sabercats vs. Arizona Rattlers)|id=2GqJAjYbAuU}}</ref>   \n|[[2002 Arena Football League season|2002]]\n|[[Wide World of Sports (U.S. TV series)|ABC]] \n|[[Tim Brant]]\n|[[Ed Cunningham]]\n|[[Lynn Swann]]\n|-\n|[[ArenaBowl XV]] \n|[[2001 Arena Football League season|2001]]\n|[[Wide World of Sports (U.S. TV series)|ABC]] \n|[[Brent Musburger